 :tx/rationale "AUDIT F-TEST-001: Tests test behavior not invariants — coverage matrix gap. PROBLEM: 2,043 tests across 13 test binaries. Tests are well-structured with clear naming. But no formal mapping from tests to specification invariants exists. Most tests verify implementation behavior ('does transact add a datom?') not specification invariants ('is INV-STORE-001 satisfied for all reachable states?'). Examples of tests that DO witness invariants: proptest_store_append_only (INV-STORE-001), kani_merge_commutative (INV-STORE-004), stateright_agent_* (protocol model checking). Examples that test behavior without INV reference: test_create_task, test_query_entity. The daemon_runtime_datoms_after_tool_calls test mentioned in audit prompt as failing is currently PASSING — fixed in prior session. JUSTIFICATION: INV-WITNESS-011 (Verification Completeness Guard) requires every invariant to have a witness at L2+. The distinction between 'behavior test' and 'invariant witness' matters: a behavior test may exercise an invariant incidentally, but an invariant witness is DESIGNED to falsify the invariant. A well-designed witness constructs adversarial inputs that stress the falsification condition. SOLUTION: (1) Add #[doc = \"Witnesses: INV-STORE-001\"] attributes to tests. (2) Generate coverage matrix via braid trace --source tests/. (3) For each Stage 0 INV without a witness, write a dedicated test. VERIFICATION: braid witness completeness shows >80% for Stage 0. DEPENDENCIES: Complements F-SPEC-001 (INV coverage), F-FORMAL-001 (Kani coverage). FILES: All test files. SEVERITY: Medium. WAVE: 3. EFFORT: 16h."
